The North Wind and the Sun disputed as to which was the more powerful, and agreed that the one who could first make a traveler take off his cloak should be called stronger. The Wind blew with all his might, but the man only wrapped his cloak about him more tightly. Then the Sun shone out warmly, and immediately the traveler took off his cloak. Thus the Sun proved that gentleness and kind persuasion win where force and bluster fail.
